
<div data-update="content" data-title="Basics">

    <!--Relative Links-->
    <h2>Links</h2>
    <p>
        All relative links are automatically hijaxed.  When clicked, a request is made, and a partial HTML update is returned.
    </p>
    <p>
        Note that all links can be hijaxed, or only selective ones via data-ajax="true".  
        Also note that links are automatically converted to "ajax links" with hash URLs.
    </p>   
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <a href="/Main/Home">Click Me</a>
    </pre>
    <a href="/Main/Home">Click Me</a>

    <hr class="line"/>   

    <!--External Links-->
    <h2>External Links</h2>
    <p>
        External links are not hijaxed.  They also open in a new window. (target="_blank")
    </p>
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <a href="http://google.com">Click Me</a>
    </pre>
    <a href="http://google.com">Click Me</a>
    <hr/>

    <hr class="line"/>

    <!--Relative Links - New Window-->
    <h2>Relative Links - New Window</h2>
    <p>
        All relative links with target="_blank" should open in new window.
    </p>
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <a href="/Main/Home" target="_blank">Click Me</a>
    </pre>
    <a href="/Main/Home" target="_blank">Click Me</a>
    
    <hr class="line"/>

    <!--Redirect-->
    <h2>Redirect</h2>
    <p>
        You can also manually redirect to a page.
    </p>
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <a href="javascript:Sync.redirect('http://google.com');">Click Me</a>
    </pre>
    <a href="javascript:Sync.redirect('http://google.com');">Click Me</a>
    
    <hr class="line"/>

    <!--Form Posts-->
    <h2>Form Posts</h2>
    <p>
        Forms are also automatically hijaxed.  Forms are also temporarily disabled to prevent double submits.
    </p>
    <label>Hijaxed form</label>
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <form method="post" action="/Post">
            <input type="text" name="PostValue" value="Hello World!" />
            <button type="submit">Save</button>
        </form>
    </pre>
    <label>Server Response</label>
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <div id="post-div" data-update="replace">
            The form was posted.  The value sent was @ViewBag.PostValue
        </div>
    </pre>
    <form method="post" action="/Post" class="box col7">
        <input type="text" name="PostValue" value="Hello World!" data-focus="false"/>
        <button type="submit">Save</button>
    </form>
    <hr />
    <div id="post-div" class="before-update-style">
        This div should be replaced after the form is posted.
    </div>

    <hr class="line" />

    <!--Confirmations-->
    <h2>Confirmations</h2>
    <p>
        You can also confirm a user action using the data-confirm attribute.
    </p>
    <pre class="brush: xml;">
        <!--Generic-->
        <a href="/Main/Home" data-confirm="true">Click Me</a>
        
        <!--Verb-->
        <a href="/Main/Home" data-confirm="return">Click Me</a>

        <!--Specific-->
        <a href="/Main/Home" data-confirm="Are you really, really sure??">Click Me</a>
    </pre>
    <a href="/Main/Home" data-confirm="true">Click Me</a> |
    <a href="/Main/Home" data-confirm="return">Click Me</a> |
    <a href="/Main/Home" data-confirm="Are you really, really sure??">Click Me</a>

    <hr class="line" />

    <!--Progress-->
    <h2>Progress Indicator</h2>
    <p>
        The framework also handles displaying the progress indicator to the user.  The indicators style can be customized via the config.
    </p>
    <a href="javascript:Sync.toggleProgress(true);">Show Progress</a> | 
    <a href="javascript:Sync.toggleProgress(false);">Hide Progress</a>

</div>
